WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:38.230 --> 00:01:44.430
Merienda

3
00:01:59.060 --> 00:02:00.000
Pâtissiers !

4
00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:01.160
Yes, sir!

5
00:02:02.140 --> 00:02:03.840
We're on our way!

6
00:02:09.050 --> 00:02:13.140
Commander Katakuri!
That was an incredible victory!

7
00:02:13.140 --> 00:02:16.660
Of course, your win was
inevitable from the beginning!

8
00:02:16.660 --> 00:02:20.320
But we were concerned
whether you could eat today's snack!

9
00:02:21.530 --> 00:02:25.400
We were all ready
and waiting at three o'clock!

10
00:02:29.780 --> 00:02:32.600
We know that you're a perfectionist
who wants to have your

11
00:02:32.600 --> 00:02:36.370
merienda at a fixed time every day,
so we understand how you must feel!

12
00:02:36.370 --> 00:02:39.010
But since it's been 40 minutes...

13
00:02:39.710 --> 00:02:43.290
your tea... has gotten cold!

14
00:02:44.530 --> 00:02:46.260
Iced tea is fine.

15
00:02:47.340 --> 00:02:49.670
He's so generous!

16
00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:52.880
In any case,
we are very proud of today's sweets!

17
00:02:52.880 --> 00:02:56.430
Here is today's merienda !

18
00:02:56.430 --> 00:02:58.970
For the perfect Commander Katakuri,

19
00:02:58.970 --> 00:03:02.890
we made it from the perfect ingredients!

20
00:03:03.410 --> 00:03:07.210
By using an abundance of the finest Corioli cacao
we could find on the black market,

21
00:03:07.210 --> 00:03:09.400
and rich cow milk,

22
00:03:09.400 --> 00:03:15.220
boasting a cortisol level below nine
and pasteurized on a sky island,

23
00:03:15.220 --> 00:03:17.570
we were able to create sweet chocolate donuts!

24
00:03:17.910 --> 00:03:18.970
And for this one,

25
00:03:18.970 --> 00:03:24.830
we whipped high-grade cream that was given to us
by Minister of Cream Opera a few days ago.

26
00:03:26.850 --> 00:03:31.190
I used a lot of haki while fighting Straw Hat.

27
00:03:32.630 --> 00:03:36.240
In order for me to take out
his fleeing crew...

28
00:03:36.810 --> 00:03:39.530
I need to restore my energy.

29
00:03:41.330 --> 00:03:43.870
Sugar is a source of power!

30
00:03:48.970 --> 00:03:50.370
I will consume it.

31
00:04:30.370 --> 00:04:32.560
I'm entering the shrine.

32
00:04:31.720 --> 00:04:32.560
Yes, sir!

33
00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:35.490
Do not let anyone in.

34
00:04:35.490 --> 00:04:40.040
Of course we won't! You will not be disturbed!
Take all the time you need!

35
00:05:10.570 --> 00:05:13.080
He's so vigilant...

36
00:05:15.390 --> 00:05:20.440
Nobody has witnessed
Commander Katakuri eating...

37
00:05:20.440 --> 00:05:25.370
What a prudent man.
When eating, a person usually lets down their guard.

38
00:05:25.370 --> 00:05:29.030
But even during teatime,
a time where people relax with others,

39
00:05:29.030 --> 00:05:35.370
he stoically concentrates his mind and supplies
his body with nutrition all on his own.

40
00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:42.170
As expected of the warrior with a bounty of over one
billion, and the foundation of the Big Mom Pirates...

41
00:05:42.170 --> 00:05:47.820
He's in a totally different class when compared
to the captain of that little pirate crew...

42
00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:48.470
Huh?

43
00:05:49.170 --> 00:05:50.220
What's wrong?

44
00:05:50.610 --> 00:05:52.440
Wasn't it there?

45
00:05:52.440 --> 00:05:53.220
What?

46
00:05:53.220 --> 00:05:55.470
Straw Hat's hand...

47
00:05:58.480 --> 00:05:59.970
W-What the?!

48
00:05:59.970 --> 00:06:01.190
What's going on?!

49
00:06:01.990 --> 00:06:03.420
The mochi is moving!

50
00:06:03.420 --> 00:06:04.710
Do you think I'm blind?!

51
00:06:04.710 --> 00:06:05.720
Why is it moving?!

52
00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:07.120
How would I know?!

53
00:06:13.620 --> 00:06:16.080
What?! Straw Hat!

54
00:06:16.690 --> 00:06:18.090
He wasn't dead?!

55
00:06:18.090 --> 00:06:19.950
How did he get out
from under all that mochi ?!

56
00:06:19.950 --> 00:06:23.000
I ate the mochi !

57
00:06:22.050 --> 00:06:23.020
What?!

58
00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:27.960
What the hell's with the way the pirates fight here?!
Do I just have to keep eating to win?!

59
00:06:27.960 --> 00:06:30.730
You're the only one
who can eat that much!

60
00:06:32.880 --> 00:06:35.450
Hey! Where'd that guy go?!

61
00:06:36.010 --> 00:06:38.510
Commander Katakuri isn't here now!

62
00:06:38.510 --> 00:06:41.340
He left the Mirro-world earlier!

63
00:06:41.340 --> 00:06:45.180
He had important business!
Now, shall we leave, too?!

64
00:06:45.180 --> 00:06:46.960
Goodbye!

65
00:06:48.660 --> 00:06:51.560
I can sense the voice
of something strong in there.

66
00:06:51.560 --> 00:06:54.030
Damn it! Observation haki?!

67
00:06:54.030 --> 00:06:55.690
So he's eating donuts?

68
00:06:55.690 --> 00:06:56.800
Sniff, sniff.

69
00:06:57.370 --> 00:06:58.820
Observation Haki?

70
00:06:58.820 --> 00:07:00.860
No, he just has a good nose...

71
00:07:01.780 --> 00:07:05.070
That bastard! He's kicking back
just because he thinks he won?!

72
00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:09.830
Don't be stupid! A fool like you is incapable
of comprehending Commander Katakuri!

73
00:07:09.830 --> 00:07:16.090
He is currently conversing
with the god of war inside the temple!

74
00:07:16.090 --> 00:07:20.760
It is a sacred time.
No one is allowed... to interrupt...

75
00:07:32.240 --> 00:07:33.690
W-What the...?

76
00:07:33.690 --> 00:07:35.650
Hey, where are you going?!

77
00:07:49.860 --> 00:07:52.570
In the end, that idiot got scared!

78
00:07:52.570 --> 00:07:55.730
It's exactly what I expected
from the captain of a weak pirate crew!

79
00:07:55.730 --> 00:07:58.140
He's only good at running away!

80
00:08:03.210 --> 00:08:04.590
He's coming back?!

81
00:08:04.590 --> 00:08:05.640
Why?!

82
00:08:06.340 --> 00:08:08.350
I'm skinny again!

83
00:08:08.350 --> 00:08:11.820
Huh?! Is the human body
 supposed to work like that?!

84
00:08:11.820 --> 00:08:16.240
All right! I'm prepared now! Here I go!

85
00:08:16.240 --> 00:08:17.780
Stop it!

86
00:08:18.110 --> 00:08:19.700
Go away, go away!

87
00:08:19.700 --> 00:08:22.030
You can't go near there!

88
00:08:24.160 --> 00:08:26.210
Gum-Gum...

89
00:08:29.960 --> 00:08:32.550
Elephant Gun!

90
00:08:38.140 --> 00:08:41.980
Commander Katakuri,
we are so very sorry!

91
00:08:45.070 --> 00:08:48.440
♪ Ahh, donuts! ♪

92
00:08:48.440 --> 00:08:51.670
♪ Yummy... donuts! ♪

93
00:08:51.670 --> 00:08:54.780
♪ Yummy to the core, donuts! ♪

94
00:08:54.780 --> 00:08:59.260
♪ While alone, I eat donuts!
Lying on my back, I eat donuts! ♪

95
00:08:59.920 --> 00:09:03.680
♪ A forbidden pleasure,
a sense of guilt, and... ♪

96
00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:05.740
♪ donuts! ♪

97
00:09:05.740 --> 00:09:08.300
This is a blissful time.

98
00:09:08.300 --> 00:09:10.470
Donuts, donuts...

99
00:09:10.470 --> 00:09:12.650
♪ Oh, donuts! ♪

100
00:09:12.650 --> 00:09:15.270
♪ So delicious, donuts! ♪

101
00:09:34.280 --> 00:09:38.560
Big Brother Katakuri is a superhuman!

102
00:09:38.560 --> 00:09:42.170
He's never laid down in his life!

103
00:09:42.170 --> 00:09:44.980
He's a man who scorns even the ground!

104
00:09:44.980 --> 00:09:47.110
He's always dignified,

105
00:09:47.110 --> 00:09:49.570
calm, and strong!

106
00:09:49.570 --> 00:09:51.870
He's the perfect human!

107
00:09:53.480 --> 00:09:57.910
That's our big brother, Katakuri!

108
00:10:06.010 --> 00:10:10.110
You saw me eating!

109
00:10:11.290 --> 00:10:14.230
Our fight hasn't ended yet!

110
00:10:31.660 --> 00:10:32.510
What?

111
00:10:43.690 --> 00:10:46.150
H-Have mercy!

112
00:10:47.010 --> 00:10:50.210
We didn't see it!
We didn't see anything!

113
00:10:50.210 --> 00:10:54.610
We won't tell anyone!
Even if our mouths are ripped apart!

114
00:10:54.610 --> 00:10:57.720
Whose mouth did you say was ripped?

115
00:10:58.060 --> 00:10:59.190
Square Mochi!

116
00:10:59.190 --> 00:11:01.170
No!

117
00:11:09.440 --> 00:11:13.720
So you're still alive! That's my mistake
for not seeing your death through to the end!

118
00:11:14.550 --> 00:11:16.730
I was at the limit of my patience!

119
00:11:31.400 --> 00:11:33.360
Ouch!

120
00:11:35.540 --> 00:11:38.160
I've got the upper hand
in armament haki, too!

121
00:11:38.900 --> 00:11:42.220
Do not think that you can stand up to me!

122
00:11:42.220 --> 00:11:45.170
You're nothing but a worm to me!

123
00:12:21.220 --> 00:12:24.720
Anyone who has seen my true form

124
00:12:25.300 --> 00:12:27.430
will die by my hand!

125
00:12:30.020 --> 00:12:30.730
Damn!

126
00:12:49.290 --> 00:12:52.040
He didn't dodge it...
and my kick landed!

127
00:12:53.860 --> 00:12:54.650
Why's that?

128
00:12:56.920 --> 00:12:59.340
So what if I got kicked?!

129
00:13:05.550 --> 00:13:07.220
I was able to ward it off easily!

130
00:13:11.990 --> 00:13:13.770
He didn't attack again right away!

131
00:13:41.850 --> 00:13:43.200
I get it now...

132
00:13:44.300 --> 00:13:46.010
your ability.

133
00:13:46.010 --> 00:13:48.390
Huh? What did you "get"?!

134
00:13:48.860 --> 00:13:53.600
I've told you several times already!
Your ability can't win against mine!

135
00:13:56.820 --> 00:13:58.190
Here I come!

136
00:14:03.040 --> 00:14:07.200
This time, I'll make sure you die!

137
00:14:14.010 --> 00:14:15.600
Gear Fourth!

138
00:14:20.180 --> 00:14:21.930
Rainfall Mochi!

139
00:14:39.290 --> 00:14:40.690
Boundman!

140
00:14:42.140 --> 00:14:45.590
You're strong but you're not invincible!

141
00:14:46.080 --> 00:14:49.410
Screw you!

142
00:15:07.670 --> 00:15:10.010
Get crushed!

143
00:15:25.860 --> 00:15:27.820
Gum-Gum...

144
00:15:30.780 --> 00:15:33.160
Kong Gun!

145
00:15:59.200 --> 00:16:01.380
I thought you were invincible!

146
00:16:07.810 --> 00:16:10.770
Because armament haki is a power
that makes things tangible...

147
00:16:13.820 --> 00:16:17.070
and because it's a power
that works even on logias...

148
00:16:26.790 --> 00:16:29.500
I thought it was weird that my attacks
passed right through your body!

149
00:16:33.290 --> 00:16:35.340
But I was wrong!

150
00:16:36.650 --> 00:16:38.300
Even you...

151
00:16:39.660 --> 00:16:41.380
can get hit!

152
00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:02.820
Despite your extremely hard armament defense...

153
00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:11.790
Gear Fourth won't lose!

154
00:17:15.080 --> 00:17:17.210
Gum-Gum...

155
00:17:19.710 --> 00:17:21.420
Culverin!

156
00:17:26.630 --> 00:17:29.840
Your mochi ability isn't what's amazing!

157
00:17:31.170 --> 00:17:33.640
It's your observation haki, isn't it?!

158
00:18:09.020 --> 00:18:11.010
Gum-Gum...

159
00:18:11.010 --> 00:18:14.680
Rhino Schneider!

160
00:18:37.510 --> 00:18:39.910
Big Brother Katakuri...

161
00:18:40.290 --> 00:18:45.920
is a superhuman whose back has never once
touched the ground since he was born!

162
00:18:56.590 --> 00:18:58.560
Gum-Gum...

163
00:18:59.770 --> 00:19:02.480
Kong Organ!

164
00:19:12.400 --> 00:19:14.200
You figured it out...

165
00:19:15.360 --> 00:19:16.830
I'm impressed.

166
00:19:18.790 --> 00:19:24.360
You're right. I just transform
to dodge your attacks efficiently.

167
00:19:25.480 --> 00:19:28.180
It's all because I can see
into the future with my haki.

168
00:19:29.650 --> 00:19:32.590
Because I was a little flustered...

169
00:19:34.350 --> 00:19:38.000
I gave you the chance to land an attack on me.

170
00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:43.030
Observation haki can't be utilized
if you're not calm.

171
00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:49.770
How many years has it been
since I last got punched?

172
00:19:59.110 --> 00:20:03.790
I'm beginning to realize
how my younger brother Cracker...

173
00:20:05.890 --> 00:20:08.210
was defeated by you.

174
00:20:08.810 --> 00:20:10.680
Is that the biscuit guy?!

175
00:20:11.240 --> 00:20:13.440
Peerless Donuts!

176
00:20:29.450 --> 00:20:33.000
It's not mochi this time?!
Screw you!

177
00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:33.710
Rhino...

178
00:20:52.110 --> 00:20:54.240
Power Mochi!

179
00:21:34.220 --> 00:21:36.510
I won't show you vulnerability a second time...

180
00:21:36.990 --> 00:21:39.350
I guess we're back to square one.

181
00:21:39.600 --> 00:21:43.100
Cacao Island

182
00:21:43.410 --> 00:21:47.650
I'm begging you!
Please open the door!

183
00:21:49.780 --> 00:21:53.450
Sweets Factory

184
00:21:53.450 --> 00:21:58.130
We can't do that, Pound-san !
Please give up and step back.

185
00:21:58.130 --> 00:22:00.390
Why not?

186
00:22:00.390 --> 00:22:02.630
Madam Pudding was very clear on this.

187
00:22:02.630 --> 00:22:06.930
I just want to get a glimpse of Chiffon!

188
00:22:06.930 --> 00:22:08.710
Who is that?

189
00:22:08.710 --> 00:22:11.440
I think he was Mama's 25th husband.

190
00:22:11.440 --> 00:22:12.930
Ah...

191
00:22:25.550 --> 00:22:28.750
I knew it was her right away!

192
00:22:33.440 --> 00:22:39.500
Chiffon hasn't changed at all
since the day she was born!

193
00:22:44.500 --> 00:22:47.270
She's as cute as she's always been!

194
00:22:47.270 --> 00:22:52.580
I just want to meet her
and exchange just a few words!

195
00:22:56.310 --> 00:22:59.560
Hey! Hey!

196
00:23:02.360 --> 00:23:04.320
Isn't it a little noisy out there?

197
00:23:06.060 --> 00:23:11.160
Some guy is yelling, huh?
But no worries. No one can come in here!

198
00:23:11.670 --> 00:23:12.990
What's wrong, Pudding?

199
00:23:13.510 --> 00:23:16.930
Nothing. Sister Brûlée, I'm listening.

200
00:23:17.270 --> 00:23:20.210
So, at one a.m. tonight,

201
00:23:20.210 --> 00:23:27.090
the Straw Hats' ship, which we lost track of,
will show up at Cacao Island!

202
00:23:27.090 --> 00:23:30.070
Here?! At one a.m.?

203
00:23:34.600 --> 00:23:38.190
The plan was to meet up
with Nami-san and the others at sea

204
00:23:38.190 --> 00:23:39.730
and hand over the wedding cake...

205
00:23:43.690 --> 00:23:46.530
Why is the Straw Hats' ship
coming to Cacao Island?

206
00:23:47.360 --> 00:23:55.490
Because that is the place where they'll rendezvous
with their separated captain, Straw Hat Luffy.

207
00:24:00.240 --> 00:24:05.540
I see... But this isn't good.
Big Mom and her children know our plan.

208
00:24:05.540 --> 00:24:07.570
Although...

209
00:24:09.530 --> 00:24:14.140
Straw Hat Luffy will never
make it to Cacao Island!

210
00:24:15.450 --> 00:24:16.930
What do you mean?

211
00:24:16.930 --> 00:24:23.520
He pushed his luck and challenged
Big Brother Katakuri to a one-on-one duel!

212
00:24:34.600 --> 00:24:39.490
So he'll definitely be defeated...
It serves him right!

213
00:24:43.540 --> 00:24:45.520
One, two!

214
00:24:48.910 --> 00:24:50.450
It's four p.m. now, isn't it?

215
00:24:51.510 --> 00:24:54.230
That means, in nine hours,

216
00:24:54.230 --> 00:24:59.720
the Straw Hat crew will arrive at Cacao Island
and wait for their captain, who'll never appear.

217
00:25:01.830 --> 00:25:07.190
And Mama on her ravenous rampage will lead herself
and Brother Peros back to Cacao Island!

218
00:25:07.190 --> 00:25:10.460
Everyone will be gathered together!

219
00:25:10.460 --> 00:25:14.490
We can't afford to fail in that situation!

220
00:25:14.490 --> 00:25:17.220
You take care of Mama, Pudding!

221
00:25:18.260 --> 00:25:20.500
You're our only hope!

222
00:25:20.500 --> 00:25:22.980
You can count on me, Sister Brûlée!

223
00:25:22.980 --> 00:25:27.040
I'll stop Mama
with the greatest wedding cake ever!

224
00:25:29.780 --> 00:25:31.760
I'm looking forward to it.

225
00:25:32.420 --> 00:25:33.710
Oh, by the way,

226
00:25:34.510 --> 00:25:38.510
even if the Straw Hats
arrive there sooner, don't worry.

227
00:25:39.650 --> 00:25:43.930
You can leave them to Big Bro Oven's troops
who just got there!

228
00:25:43.930 --> 00:25:47.850
What?! Big Bro Oven's here?!

229
00:25:53.860 --> 00:25:55.070
It's Minister Oven!

230
00:25:55.070 --> 00:25:56.150
Minister Oven!

231
00:25:56.360 --> 00:26:02.370
Charlotte Oven
4th Son of the Charlotte Family
Minister of Browned Food

232
00:25:56.460 --> 00:25:59.660
What do you mean I can't enter the factory?!

233
00:25:59.660 --> 00:26:03.130
Those were Madam Pudding's orders...

234
00:26:03.130 --> 00:26:04.340
Not even me?!

235
00:26:04.340 --> 00:26:05.770
Correct, no one.

236
00:26:05.770 --> 00:26:09.000
Well, if that's what my little sister wants,
I'll accept it.

237
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:13.070
Also, why is it so noisy
in front of the factory?!

238
00:26:13.070 --> 00:26:15.670
What? Oh, that's because...

239
00:26:16.360 --> 00:26:19.550
Hey! Chiffon!

240
00:26:20.060 --> 00:26:21.520
That guy's...

241
00:26:30.980 --> 00:26:34.530
S-Stop hurting me!

242
00:26:34.530 --> 00:26:36.650
Shut up, weirdo!

243
00:26:36.650 --> 00:26:40.700
D-Don't you remember me, Oven-kun ?!

244
00:26:42.240 --> 00:26:45.650
I remember you, my former stepfather.

245
00:26:45.650 --> 00:26:51.060
I-I'm happy that you remember me.

246
00:26:51.060 --> 00:26:55.550
I used to be your stepfather.

247
00:26:59.400 --> 00:27:01.430
That's why I must remove you.

248
00:27:01.430 --> 00:27:02.550
What?

249
00:27:04.700 --> 00:27:07.290
I wonder who's making that racket outside...

250
00:27:07.700 --> 00:27:09.170
Is it bothering you?

251
00:27:09.170 --> 00:27:11.710
Sanji-san ! Were you listening?

252
00:27:11.710 --> 00:27:12.610
Yeah.

253
00:27:12.610 --> 00:27:14.510
Luffy-kun is in trouble!

254
00:27:14.510 --> 00:27:15.590
Right.

255
00:27:15.590 --> 00:27:18.830
I can't believe he's fighting one-on-one
with Brother Katakuri.

256
00:27:18.830 --> 00:27:21.320
That's too reckless!

257
00:27:21.320 --> 00:27:22.220
I bet so.

258
00:27:22.220 --> 00:27:26.650
Brother Katakuri is a superhuman!
His bounty is over one billion!

259
00:27:26.650 --> 00:27:30.660
He's never been defeated!
What should we do?!

260
00:27:31.670 --> 00:27:33.240
Then today...

261
00:27:35.010 --> 00:27:37.270
he'll lose for the first time.

262
00:27:38.200 --> 00:27:40.840
What we've got to do now is...

263
00:27:40.840 --> 00:27:43.770
make the greatest cake ever, right?

264
00:27:48.660 --> 00:27:51.180
Your stupid friend...

265
00:27:51.180 --> 00:27:55.870
will be completely destroyed
at the hands of Brother Katakuri!

266
00:27:56.350 --> 00:27:57.370
Sanji...

267
00:27:58.850 --> 00:27:59.980
Pudding-chan.

268
00:28:00.660 --> 00:28:04.050
It's okay. Let's make the cake.

269
00:28:04.650 --> 00:28:08.500
This is our first joint project, isn't it?

270
00:28:13.530 --> 00:28:14.220
...-san !

271
00:28:14.220 --> 00:28:17.050
Whoa! Madam Pudding is steaming!

272
00:28:17.050 --> 00:28:18.380
Did someone bake her?!

273
00:28:18.380 --> 00:28:19.260
No way!

274
00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:24.490
Madam Pudding!

275
00:28:26.660 --> 00:28:30.040
The Sunny
At Sea

276
00:28:30.040 --> 00:28:32.380
No one's coming after us!

277
00:28:32.380 --> 00:28:38.010
This is odd. In this region of the sea,
there's no way pursuers won't come!

278
00:28:38.010 --> 00:28:39.800
What do you think is happening?

279
00:28:39.800 --> 00:28:41.680
It has to be a trap!

280
00:28:41.680 --> 00:28:46.220
Don't worry! We won't let our guards down
for even a single moment!

281
00:28:46.220 --> 00:28:50.740
By the way, I wonder if
Aladine and the others are okay...

282
00:28:51.390 --> 00:28:54.380
I hope they got away safely...

283
00:28:54.380 --> 00:28:56.250
What?!

284
00:28:56.250 --> 00:29:01.460
Mama is destroying Nuts Island?!
What do you mean by that, Big Bro Peros?!

285
00:29:01.460 --> 00:29:03.130
Well, I mean...!

286
00:29:03.130 --> 00:29:06.140
Minister Mont d'Or!
We have a problem!

287
00:29:06.140 --> 00:29:10.270
What is it this time?!
We already have enough problems!

288
00:29:10.710 --> 00:29:14.640
By looking under the sea...
we found out a terrible truth...

289
00:29:17.390 --> 00:29:18.690
The thing is...

290
00:29:18.690 --> 00:29:21.150
– Wha...?!
– Cock-a...?!

291
00:29:21.150 --> 00:29:25.070
All the territorial sea slugs are gone?!

292
00:29:25.070 --> 00:29:26.690
Why?!

293
00:29:26.690 --> 00:29:28.570
Are they all dead-jour ?!

294
00:29:28.570 --> 00:29:30.330
Not a single one left?!

295
00:29:30.870 --> 00:29:31.950
I don't know...

296
00:29:31.950 --> 00:29:36.930
There were tens of thousands of them!
How could they be gone all of a sudden?!

297
00:29:37.790 --> 00:29:39.510
M-Maybe they were kidnapped?

298
00:29:39.510 --> 00:29:41.320
By who, you idiot?!

299
00:29:41.320 --> 00:29:44.680
In that case, the enemy ships
can go wherever they like!

300
00:29:44.680 --> 00:29:46.050
Do something!

301
00:29:46.890 --> 00:29:48.910
L-Like what...?

302
00:29:48.910 --> 00:29:52.860
Find out why they're gone! Hurry up!

303
00:29:52.860 --> 00:29:54.240
Y-Yes, sir!

304
00:30:10.240 --> 00:30:14.750
♪ Come on, let's sing together! ♪

305
00:30:14.750 --> 00:30:19.420
♪ Little sea slugs! ♪

306
00:30:19.420 --> 00:30:24.090
♪ When you stop working... ♪

307
00:30:24.090 --> 00:30:28.640
♪ you'll be much happier! ♪

308
00:30:28.640 --> 00:30:30.760
♪ Security? I forbid it! ♪

309
00:30:30.760 --> 00:30:33.180
♪ Reporting? I forbid it! ♪

310
00:30:33.180 --> 00:30:36.310
♪ But singing is... ♪

311
00:30:36.310 --> 00:30:38.550
♪ okay! ♪

312
00:30:45.840 --> 00:30:50.080
♪ Yes, you shouldn't be working! ♪

313
00:30:54.990 --> 00:31:02.130
♪ That's the rule... for a day off! ♪
